reviews.review: First of all, I wanted to say that it's pretty much a cash grab. They said "oh yeah throw a little bit of emoji swag in there, some YouTube crap, famous actors, instagram, twitter, dank memes, all the good stuff." Most of the joke were pretty bland and unfunny. To be honest, I smiled twice and I don't even remember when. See, that's how forgettable this movie was. It just like they didn't care. Don't get me wrong, the animation it pretty nice. But that's like the only good thing in this movie. I guess it had some sort of charm to it? I don't know, I guess I'm just giving 3 starts cause I'm nice.

This movie is absolutely awe-inspiring. Never have I seen such a masterful piece of cinema. The pure EMOJtions that this movie conveys are so real and visceral. I can't describe what makes this movie so utterly amazing, but what I can say is that you need to see this movie right this instant. Unless you haven't a single brain cell, you'll see this movie right now. A magnum opus for all of cinema. A pop masterpiece.
